# Skills Development Rules for newth-skills

## Project Context
- Repository: n3wth/newth-skills
- Type: AI skill discovery and distribution platform
- Tech: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite, Tailwind CSS, GSAP animations
- Site: skills.newth.ai - Skills for Claude Code, Gemini CLI, and other AI assistants

## Skill Implementation Standards

### Skill Structure
Every skill must follow the `.skill` package format:
```
skill-name.skill/
├── SKILL.md                    # Frontmatter + documentation (required)
├── scripts/
│   └── <script>py/sh          # Executable scripts (Python or Bash)
├── templates/
│   └── <template>.md           # Configuration or code templates
├── references/
│   └── <guide>.md              # API guides, documentation
└── assets/
    └── <visual>png/svg         # Optional visual assets
```

### SKILL.md Frontmatter (Required)
```yaml
---
name: Skill Display Name
slug: skill-slug
description: One-line description
author: Oliver Newth
repo: n3wth/newth-skills
version: 1.0.0
categories: [category1, category2]
platforms: [claude-code, gemini-cli]
status: stable
tags: [tag1, tag2]
---
```

### Categories
Choose from: `development`, `documents`, `creative`, `productivity`, `business`

### Skill Types
Based on created issues (#126-141):

**Workspace & Configuration (4 skills)**
- Cursor Project Bootstrapper
- AI Rules Manager
- Extension Sync Tool
- Cursor Agent Orchestrator

**Development Workflow (3 skills)**
- Code Generation Pipeline
- Cursor-Driven Refactoring
