## Code Quality Standards

### Python Scripts
- Use standard library where possible (avoid dependencies)
- Type hints on all functions
- Error handling with clear messages
- Executable with `python3 script.py [args]`
- Include --help documentation

### Bash Scripts
- Use `#!/bin/bash` header
- Clear error messages
- Exit codes: 0 (success), 1 (error)
- Executable with `bash script.sh [args]`

### Templates & Guides
- Markdown format only
- Include YAML/JSON examples where applicable
- Comment all configuration with rationale
- Provide copy-paste ready snippets

## Site Integration

### Skill Registration
New skills are added to `src/data/skills.ts`:
```typescript
{
  id: 'skill-slug',
  name: 'Skill Name',
  category: 'category',
  description: 'Brief description',
  author: 'Oliver Newth',
  tags: ['tag1', 'tag2'],
  command: 'install-command',
  links: { ... }
}
```

### Data Source
Skills data lives in:
- `src/data/skills.ts` - Main registry
- `skills/` directory - Skill definitions (markdown + YAML)

## Development Workflow

### For Implementing Skills
1. Create feature branch: `feature/skill-<name>`
2. Implement skill in `.skill` package format
3. Add to `src/data/skills.ts`
4. Test with actual installation commands
5. Update `skills/` directory markdown
6. Create PR with skill demo/examples
7. Merge to main via fast-forward

### For Copilot Agent Use
Commands to delegate Cursor skill development to Copilot:
```bash
# Assign issue to Copilot agent
gh issue edit <issue_num> --add-assignee copilot-swe-agent[bot]

# With custom agent setup skill
/copilot-agent-setup --assign-issue <issue_num> --agent workspace-expert
```

## Design Consistency

### Naming
- Skills: kebab-case (e.g., `cursor-project-bootstrapper`)
- Categories: lowercase (development, documents, creative, productivity, business)
- Scripts: snake_case.py or kebab-case.sh

### Documentation
- Keep descriptions under 100 characters
- Use active voice ("Create workspaces..." not "Used for creating...")
- Include real usage examples
- Document all command-line arguments

## Testing & Validation

### Before Submitting PR
- Test skill installation on clean environment
- Verify all scripts execute without errors
- Check SKILL.md YAML syntax validity
- Ensure markdown renders correctly on GitHub
- Validate that site build passes (`npm run build`)

### CI/CD
GitHub Actions validate:
- TypeScript compilation (`npm run build`)
- ESLint (`npm run lint`)
- Skill data integrity
- SKILL.md frontmatter correctness

## Copilot Integration

### Assign New Skill Issues to Copilot
Use the copilot-agent-setup skill:
```bash
npm run copilot -- --assign-issue 126 --model claude-opus-4-5 --agent workspace-expert
```

### Agent Models Available
- `claude-opus-4-5` (powerful, best for complex skills)
- `claude-sonnet-4` (balanced, good for most skills)
- `claude-haiku-4.5` (fast, suitable for templates/docs)

### Custom Instructions for Copilot
Pass via agent setup or embedded in issue:
```
Focus on: [skill-specific area]
Constraints: [technical limits]
Testing: [validation approach]
```

